# Admin Feature Development Guidelines

When creating new admin functionality (pages, dashboards, tools) under `/app/admin/`, you MUST complete ALL of the following steps:

## Required Checklist

### 1. Create the Admin Page
- Create the page at `app/admin/{feature}/page.tsx`
- Use the existing admin UI patterns (dark theme, gradient cards, etc.)
- Wrap with `<ProtectedRoute requireAdmin>` for access control

### 2. Add Navigation to Admin Dashboard
**CRITICAL: This step is mandatory and must not be skipped.**

After creating any new admin page, you MUST add a Quick Action card to the main admin dashboard at `app/admin/page.tsx`:

```tsx
<Link href="/admin/{feature}">
  <motion.div
    whileHover={{ scale: 1.02 }}
    className="p-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-{color}-600/20 to-{color2}-600/20 border border-{color}-500/50 rounded-xl cursor-pointer"
  >
    <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
      <div className="w-16 h-16 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-{color}-600 to-{color2}-600 flex items-center justify-center">
        <{Icon} size={32} className="text-white" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 className="text-xl font-bold mb-1">{Feature Name}</h3>
        <p className="text-gray-400 text-sm">{Brief description}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </motion.div>
</Link>
```

Also add the icon import at the top of the file from `lucide-react`.

### 3. Update Any Relevant Documentation
- If the feature requires setup (database schema, env vars, etc.), document it
- Update README or create a setup guide if needed

## Color Palette for Admin Cards

Use these gradient combinations for consistency:
- **Chat/Communication**: amber → orange
- **Analytics/Data**: purple → pink  
- **Content/Settings**: blue → cyan
- **Users/Management**: green → teal
- **System/Config**: cyan → blue
- **Sales/Revenue**: emerald → teal
- **Testing/QA**: rose → red
- **Alerts/Warnings**: yellow → orange

## Plan Template

When planning new admin features, include this section:

```
### Admin Dashboard Integration
- [ ] Add Quick Action card to `/app/admin/page.tsx`
- [ ] Import icon from lucide-react
- [ ] Choose appropriate gradient colors
- [ ] Write concise description
```

## Why This Matters

Admin features that aren't visible from the dashboard are effectively hidden and unusable. Users expect to discover and access all admin functionality from the central dashboard.
